{!<div class="typewriter dialogue5">!}

= 1982, Taking the Cowl

It’s been a few weeks since you’ve returned to Gotham. 

The place has not changed since the incident. 

Their portraits, they stared back with the same intensity as they did the first day you swore your duties.

“Father,"

"I’ve gathered the means.”

“I do not know how to think it.”

“I know what to do,"

"make them afraid.”

“I have wealth, 
I have power,
I’ve got everything.
 A call from the night.”

“I’ve seen it,
crashing through the window,
through our life, 

through what remains.”

“A sentinel of ruins,

a watcher in the dark.”

“Father, 

I will be the bat.”

“But something's 

missing…”

“Something isn’t right.”

“I have to know, 

I have to.”

“I have to know what’s in me, 

driving me forward.”

“I have to know why the cowl chose me.”

“I have to know.”

“What does this cowl mean?”

{!</div>!}

- @liberty: Saying Yes to anyone in Authority, anyone with a badge. My parents taught me something else, lying cold on the pavement. They taught me that the world only makes sense when you force it to.
- @order: Nothing helps one put problems in perspective like allegiance to a higher cause. The Law provides that a man is innocent until proven guilty, and we must abide by it.
- @morality: Vengeance blackens the soul. I've always feared that I would become that which I fought against. I walk the edge of that abyss every night, but I haven't fallen in and I thank heaven for that.

@liberty
on-arrival: order -= 1
go-to: 1983

